Looks like there were multiple eucalyptus-cloud processes running:

{code}
# ps aux | grep eucalyptus-cloud
root     10982  0.0  0.0  13792   220 ?        Ss   14:08   0:00 eucalyptus-cloud
eucalyp+ 11064  9.8 43.1 9041680 3453096 ?     Sl   14:09   7:34 eucalyptus-cloud
eucalyp+ 14979  7.0 38.4 9315956 3078752 ?     Sl   Jun14 123:24 eucalyptus-cloud
root     21380  0.0  0.0 112652   976 pts/1    S+   15:26   0:00 grep --color=auto eucalyptus-cloud
{code}

I stopped all instances and then restarted the eucalyptus-cloud service. It looks as though the equallogic provider should be available now:

{code}
# euctl euca='com.eucalyptus.blockstorage.StorageManagers.providers' 
{ceph-rbd=class com.eucalyptus.blockstorage.ceph.CephRbdProvider, equallogic=class com.eucalyptus.blockstorage.san.equallogic.EquallogicProvider}
{code}

I did not try to configure it.

We may want to reopen EUCA-12440 if we are still seeing issues with the service.
